1. What is React

Solution:
 React is a JS library created by fb for building UI's

 2. What is useMemo ?

Solution: 
useMemo is hook used to memoize certain expensive cALculations so tat performance is optimized

example :

import React,{useState} from 'react'

const App = () =>
{
  const [counterOne,setCounterOne] = useState(0);
const [counterTwo,setCounterTwo] = useState(0);
const isEven = () =>
{
while(i<2000000000) i++
 return counterOne % 2 === 0 
}
return(
<div>
<button onClick={()=>setCounterOne(counterOne + 1)}>Counter1 - {counterOne}</button>
<span>{isEven() ? 'Even' : 'Odd'}</span>
<button onClick={()=>setCounterTwo(counterTwo + 1)}>Counter2 - {counterTwo}</button>
</div>
)
}

export default App;

first with the above code on click of counterone button , counter1 increments slowly
bcoz of the time taking expensive calculation it is valid only but on click of counterTwo
button also there will be time delay in incrementation of counter two it is bcoz each time
counterTwo is pressed value changes and re-rendering happens and each time isEven is executed
tat's why the delay to solve it we use useMemo where we cache the result and cause re-render
only when there is change in state variable

below is the proper solution with optimization using useMemo

import React,{useState,useMemo} from 'react'

const App = () =>
{
  const [counterOne,setCounterOne] = useState(0);
const [counterTwo,setCounterTwo] = useState(0);
const isEven = useMemo(() =>
{
while(i<2000000000) i++
 return counterOne % 2 === 0 
},[counterOne])
return(
<div>
<button onClick={()=>setCounterOne(counterOne + 1)}>Counter1 - {counterOne}</button>
<span>{isEven ? 'Even' : 'Odd'}</span>
<button onClick={()=>setCounterTwo(counterTwo + 1)}>Counter2 - {counterTwo}</button>
</div>
)
}

export default App;

with the above solution the performance is improved


 

export default App;


